root>mongo  --> to login into the shell

show dbs --> to show all the dbs available in this installation

show dbs

use <db>  -->for selecting db

show collections --> to show all the list of the collections(analogyes to table in rdbms) in this database.

db.<collection>.count() --> to know the list of records available.

db.<collection>.find() --> to list all the records of that collections

it --> to iterate over the result in shell.

db.<collection>.find({<field>:<value>}) --> to find the items which match to a particular criteria

db.<collection>.remove(); -->removes all the items from collection.











